# Sandugach, Yanaulsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Sandugach (; , HanduÄŸas) is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative centre of Sandugachevsky Selsoviet, Yanaulsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 431 as of 2010. There are 9 streets.
Geography
Sandugach is located 19&nbsp;km east of Yanaul (the district's administrative centre) by road. Barabanovka is the nearest rural locality.
